The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning agents to perform a physical construction task, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The focus on relational inductive bias and structured reasoning suggests a strong emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of object-centric and relation-centric scene representations suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the application of the agent to a physical task suggests a potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
